### File Structure
```
OnlineCourse/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── course_catalog.html
│   ├── course_details.html
│   ├── my_courses.html
│   ├── course_learning.html
│   ├── my_assignments.html
│   ├── submit_assignment.html
│   ├── certificates.html
│   └── user_profile.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   └── js/
│       └── scripts.js
│
└── data/
    ├── users.txt
    ├── courses.txt
    ├── enrollments.txt
    ├── assignments.txt
    ├── submissions.txt
    └── certificates.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python file containing the web application logic using a web framework (e.g., Flask). It handles routing, page rendering, data processing, and file I/O operations for all pages and functionalities described in the requirements.

- templates/
  Directory containing HTML template files for each of the nine pages defined in the requirements. These templates include the specified elements with their IDs and structure, and are rendered dynamically by app.py.

  - dashboard.html
    Template for the Dashboard page showing welcome message, enrolled courses, and navigation buttons.

  - course_catalog.html
    Template for browsing and searching available courses with course cards and navigation.

  - course_details.html
    Template showing detailed course information and enrollment button with conditional states.

  - my_courses.html
    Template listing enrolled courses with progress and continue learning buttons.

  - course_learning.html
    Template for viewing lessons, lesson content, marking completion, and progress tracking.

  - my_assignments.html
    Template displaying assignments table with submission buttons.

  - submit_assignment.html
    Template for submitting assignment text responses and confirmation messages.

  - certificates.html
    Template showing earned certificates in a grid with navigation.

  - user_profile.html
    Template for viewing and editing user profile information.

- static/
  Directory for static assets like CSS and JavaScript files.

  - css/styles.css
    Stylesheet for consistent styling of all pages and UI elements.

  - js/scripts.js
    JavaScript file for client-side interactivity, such as button actions and form validations.

- data/
  Directory containing all local text files used for data storage as specified.

  - users.txt
    Stores user information (username, email, fullname).

  - courses.txt
    Stores course details.

  - enrollments.txt
    Stores enrollment records with progress tracking.

  - assignments.txt
    Stores assignment details.

  - submissions.txt
    Stores assignment submissions and grading info.

  - certificates.txt
    Stores issued certificates for completed courses.
```
